ity and our damping parameter rule on\nthe numerical complexity of the quadrature methods. Moreover, we reveal that\nour approach achieves substantial computational gains compared to the Monte\nCarlo method for different dimensions and parameter constellations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Mar 2022 18:48:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 25 Aug 2022 17:38:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-26"}
