 by an enhanced residual symmetry. We\nelucidate these results with representative examples of flavour and CP\nsymmetries, which all lead to a good agreement with the measured lepton mixing\nangles and, possibly, the current hint of the CP phase $\\delta$. We identify\nthe CP-violating combinations relevant for low-scale leptogenesis, and show\nthat the parametric dependence of the BAU found numerically can be understood\nwell with their help.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Mar 2022 11:02:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 19 Dec 2022 16:17:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-20"}
